    "potentialSeverity": "1",
    "sourceColumn": "Corrective Actions",
    "actionItemText": "Regulatory Reference:"
  },
  {
    "incidentNo": "38",
    "dateTimeOccurred": "2025-09-27T00:00:00.000Z",
    "site": "CERCINA",
    "actualSeverity": "1",
    "potentialSeverity": "1",
    "sourceColumn": "Corrective Actions",
    "actionItemText": "1-As per SOLAS Chapter V, Regulation 22, coastal States are required to ensure that aids to navigation (including buoys) are maintained in proper working condition. Although SOLAS does not prescribe a specific time interval for inspections, international best practices recommend that floating navigational aids be inspected at least once every 12 months."
  },
  {
    "incidentNo": "38",
    "dateTimeOccurred": "2025-09-27T00:00:00.000Z",
    "site": "CERCINA",
    "actualSeverity": "1",
    "potentialSeverity": "1",
    "sourceColumn": "Corrective Actions",
    "actionItemText": "2-Additionally, organizations like the IALA (International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities) suggest: Buoy systems should be inspected and serviced annually or as defined by risk-based maintenance programs."
  },
